Drain and rinse @black beans{1%13.4oz can}.

Pat @chicken breast strips{10%oz} dry with paper towels.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a #medium pan{} over medium-high
heat. Add beans, chicken, and @Southwest spice blend{1%tbsp}. Cook,
stirring occasionally, until chicken is browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Season with a big pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{} and set aside. Wipe out pan.

Place @flour tortillas{2} on a clean work surface. Evenly sprinkle
@pepper jack cheese{1/2%cup} onto one half of each tortilla. Top with
chicken and bean filling, then sprinkle with @Monterey Jack cheese{1/4%cup}. Fold tortillas in half to create quesadillas.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for filling over medium
heat. Add quesadillas and cook until tortillas are golden
brown and cheese melts, ~{3-4%minutes}. 

> TIP: Depending on the size of your pan, you may need to work in batches.

Cut quesadillas into wedges and divide between plates. Top with
@sour cream{2%tbsp} and serve.